tion of history and historiographic research, and for this sense of history to expand our conception of art, in turn. At stake in this consideration is the possibility of a new, materially based philosophy of history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aHistoryxPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophy, Italian. 4aArea Studies : Italian Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Art. 4aHistory : Historiography. 4aPhilosophy : Aesthetics. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Individual Philosophers.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849159240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438491592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438491592/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles